{"Name":"Create Event","Description":"Create a new event in MISP.","Script":"# Copyright 2026 Google LLC\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\nfrom SiemplifyUtils import output_handler\nfrom SiemplifyAction import SiemplifyAction\nfrom ScriptResult import EXECUTION_STATE_COMPLETED, EXECUTION_STATE_FAILED\nfrom MISPManager import MISPManager\nfrom TIPCommon.extraction import extract_action_param, extract_configuration_param\nfrom exceptions import MISPNotAcceptableNumberOrStringError, MISPManagerCreateEventError\nfrom constants import (\n    INTEGRATION_NAME,\n    CREATE_EVENT_SCRIPT_NAME,\n    DISTRIBUTION,\n    COMMUNITY,\n    THREAT_LEVEL,\n    HIGH,\n    ANALYSIS,\n    INITIAL,\n)\n\n\n@output_handler\ndef main():\n    siemplify = SiemplifyAction()\n    siemplify.script_name = CREATE_EVENT_SCRIPT_NAME\n\n    siemplify.LOGGER.info(\"----------------- Main - Param Init -----------------\")\n\n    # INIT INTEGRATION CONFIGURATION:\n    api_root = extract_configuration_param(\n        siemplify, provider_name=INTEGRATION_NAME, param_name=\"Api Root\"\n    )\n    api_token = extract_configuration_param(\n        siemplify, provider_name=INTEGRATION_NAME, param_name=\"Api Key\"\n    )\n    use_ssl = extract_configuration_param(\n        siemplify,\n        provider_name=INTEGRATION_NAME,\n        param_name=\"Use SSL\",\n        default_value=False,\n        input_type=bool,\n    )\n    ca_certificate = extract_configuration_param(\n        siemplify,\n        provider_name=INTEGRATION_NAME,\n        param_name=\"CA Certificate File - parsed into Base64 String\",\n    )\n    siemplify.LOGGER.info(\"----------------- Main - Started -----------------\")\n    # INIT ACTION PARAMETERS:\n    event_name = extract_action_param(\n        siemplify, param_name=\"Event Name\", is_mandatory=True, print_value=True\n    )\n    distribution = extract_action_param(\n        siemplify,\n        param_name=\"Distribution\",\n        print_value=True,\n        default_value=str(DISTRIBUTION[COMMUNITY]),\n    )\n    threat_level = extract_action_param(\n        siemplify,\n        param_name=\"Threat Level\",\n        print_value=True,\n        default_value=str(THREAT_LEVEL[HIGH]),\n    )\n    analysis = extract_action_param(\n        siemplify,\n        param_name=\"Analysis\",\n        print_value=True,\n        default_value=str(ANALYSIS[INITIAL]),\n    )\n    publish = extract_action_param(\n        siemplify,\n        param_name=\"Publish\",\n        print_value=True,\n        input_type=bool,\n        default_value=False,\n    )\n    comment = extract_action_param(siemplify, param_name=\"Comment\", print_value=True)\n\n    result_value = False\n    status = EXECUTION_STATE_COMPLETED\n    is_published_successfully = False\n    output_message = \"\"\n\n    try:\n        if distribution.lower() not in map(\n            str, tuple(DISTRIBUTION.keys()) + tuple(DISTRIBUTION.values())\n        ):\n            raise MISPNotAcceptableNumberOrStringError(\n                \"Distribution\",\n                acceptable_strings=DISTRIBUTION.keys(),\n                acceptable_numbers=DISTRIBUTION.values(),\n            )\n        distribution = int(\n            DISTRIBUTION[distribution.lower()]\n            if not distribution.isdigit()\n            else distribution\n        )\n\n        if threat_level.lower() not in map(\n            str, tuple(THREAT_LEVEL.keys()) + tuple(THREAT_LEVEL.values())\n        ):\n            raise MISPNotAcceptableNumberOrStringError(\n                \"Threat Level\",\n                acceptable_strings=THREAT_LEVEL.keys(),\n                acceptable_numbers=THREAT_LEVEL.values(),\n            )\n        threat_level = int(\n            THREAT_LEVEL[threat_level.lower()]\n            if not threat_level.isdigit()\n            else threat_level\n        )\n\n        if analysis.lower() not in map(\n            str, tuple(ANALYSIS.keys()) + tuple(ANALYSIS.values())\n        ):\n            raise MISPNotAcceptableNumberOrStringError(\n                \"Analysis\",\n                acceptable_strings=ANALYSIS.keys(),\n                acceptable_numbers=ANALYSIS.values(),\n            )\n        analysis = int(\n            ANALYSIS[analysis.lower()] if not analysis.isdigit() else analysis\n        )\n\n        manager = MISPManager(api_root, api_token, use_ssl, ca_certificate)\n\n        siemplify.LOGGER.info(f\"Creating new event in {INTEGRATION_NAME}\")\n        event = manager.create_event(\n            event_name=event_name,\n            distribution=distribution,\n            analysis=analysis,\n            threat_level=threat_level,\n            comment=comment,\n        )\n        event_id = event.id\n        siemplify.LOGGER.info(\n            f\"Successfully created event {event_id} in {INTEGRATION_NAME}.\"\n        )\n\n        if publish:\n            try:\n                siemplify.LOGGER.info(\n                    f\"Publishing event {event_id} in {INTEGRATION_NAME}\"\n                )\n                event = manager.publish_event(event_id=event_id)\n                is_published_successfully = True\n                siemplify.LOGGER.info(\n                    f\"Successfully published event {event_id} in {INTEGRATION_NAME}.\"\n                )\n\n            except Exception as error:\n                result_value = False\n                output_message = f\"Event {event_id} was created, but it wasn't published. Reason: {error}\"\n                siemplify.LOGGER.error(output_message)\n                siemplify.LOGGER.exception(error)\n\n        if (publish and is_published_successfully) or not publish:\n            output_message = (\n                f\"Successfully created event {event_id} in {INTEGRATION_NAME}.\"\n            )\n\n        result_value = event_id\n        siemplify.result.add_result_json(event.to_json())\n    except MISPManagerCreateEventError:\n        output_message = (\n            f\"Action wasn’t able to create new event in {INTEGRATION_NAME}.\"\n        )\n    except Exception as e:\n        status = EXECUTION_STATE_FAILED\n        result_value = False\n        output_message = (\n            f\"Error executing action '{CREATE_EVENT_SCRIPT_NAME}'. Reason: {e}\"\n        )\n        siemplify.LOGGER.error(output_message)\n        siemplify.LOGGER.exception(e)\n\n    siemplify.LOGGER.info(\"----------------- Main - Finished -----------------\")\n    siemplify.LOGGER.info(\n        f\"\\n  status: {status}\\n  result_value: {result_value}\\n  output_message: {output_message}\"\n    )\n    siemplify.end(output_message, result_value, status)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n","IntegrationIdentifier":"MISP","ScriptResultName":"event_id","DynamicResultsMetadata":[{"ResultName":"JsonResult","ResultExample":"{\"id\": \"XXX\", \"orgc_id\": \"1\", \"org_id\": \"1\", \"date\": \"2020-12-21\", \"threat_level_id\": \"1\", \"info\": \"qweqwe\", \"published\": false, \"uuid\": \"e8c5c0adXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXd62c06ee\", \"attribute_count\": \"0\", \"analysis\": \"1\", \"timestamp\": \"1608536549\", \"distribution\": \"0\", \"proposal_email_lock\": false, \"locked\": false, \"publish_timestamp\": \"0\", \"sharing_group_id\": \"0\", \"disable_correlation\": false, \"extends_uuid\": \"\", \"event_creator_email\": \"admin@admin.test\", \"Org\": {\"id\": \"1\", \"name\": \"ORGNAME\", \"uuid\": \"09b0dde1-2934XXXXXXXXXXXXXX6f534f041\", \"local\": true}, \"Orgc\": {\"id\": \"1\", \"name\": \"ORGNAME\", \"uuid\": \"09b0dde1-2934XXXXXXXXXXXXXX6f534f041\", \"local\": true}}","ShowResult":true}],"Creator":"admin","IsEnabled":true,"IsCustom":true,"AiGenerated":false,"IsSystem":false,"Version":0.0,"TimeoutSeconds":600,"IsAsync":false,"AsyncPollingIntervalInSeconds":300,"TotalIntervalTimeoutForAsyncInSeconds":3600,"Parameters":[{"CustomActionId":0,"IsMandatory":true,"DefaultValue":"","Description":"Specify the name for the new event.","Name":"Event Name","Value":"","Type":0,"OptionalValues":null,"OptionalValuesJson":null},{"CustomActionId":0,"IsMandatory":false,"DefaultValue":"Community","Description":"Specify the distribution of the event. Possible values: 0 - Organisation, 1 - Community, 2 - Connected, 3 - All. You can either provide a number or a string.","Name":"Distribution","Value":"Community","Type":0,"OptionalValues":null,"OptionalValuesJson":null},{"CustomActionId":0,"IsMandatory":false,"DefaultValue":"High","Description":"Specify the threat level of the event. Possible values: 1 - High, 2 - Medium, 3 - Low, 4 - Undefined. You can either provide a number or a string.","Name":"Threat Level","Value":"High","Type":0,"OptionalValues":null,"OptionalValuesJson":null},{"CustomActionId":0,"IsMandatory":false,"DefaultValue":"Initial","Description":"Specify the analysis of the event. Possible values: 0 - Initial, 1 - Ongoing, 2 - Completed. You can either provide a number or a string.","Name":"Analysis","Value":"Initial","Type":0,"OptionalValues":null,"OptionalValuesJson":null},{"CustomActionId":0,"IsMandatory":false,"DefaultValue":"false","Description":"If enabled, action will publish the event to the community.","Name":"Publish","Value":"false","Type":1,"OptionalValues":null,"OptionalValuesJson":null},{"CustomActionId":0,"IsMandatory":false,"DefaultValue":"","Description":"Specify additional comments related to the event.","Name":"Comment","Value":"","Type":0,"OptionalValues":null,"OptionalValuesJson":null}],"DefaultResultValue":null,"PythonVersion":"None","ActionType":1,"SimulationData":{"Entities":null},"SimulationDataJson":null,"AICategories":[],"OutcomeCategories":[],"AIDescription":"### General Description\nCreates a new event in the MISP (Malware Information Sharing Platform) instance. This action allows users to programmatically generate events to store threat intelligence, specifying details such as threat levels, distribution scope, and analysis status. It can also optionally publish the event to the MISP community immediately upon creation.\n\n### Parameters Description\n| Parameter | Type | Mandatory | Description |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Event Name** | String | Yes | The name or 'info' field for the new MISP event. |\n| **Distribution** | String/Integer | No | Specifies the distribution scope. Possible values: 0 (Organisation), 1 (Community), 2 (Connected), 3 (All). Defaults to 'Community'. |\n| **Threat Level** | String/Integer | No | Specifies the threat level. Possible values: 1 (High), 2 (Medium), 3 (Low), 4 (Undefined). Defaults to 'High'. |\n| **Analysis** | String/Integer | No | Specifies the analysis stage. Possible values: 0 (Initial), 1 (Ongoing), 2 (Completed). Defaults to 'Initial'. |\n| **Publish** | Boolean | No | If enabled (True), the action will publish the event to the community after creation. Defaults to False. |\n| **Comment** | String | No | Additional comments or notes related to the event. |\n\n### Additional Notes\n- The action accepts both numeric IDs and string labels (e.g., 'High' or '1') for Distribution, Threat Level, and Analysis parameters.\n- If 'Publish' is set to True but the publication step fails, the action will still report success for the event creation but will include the publication error in the output message.\n\n### Flow Description\n1. **Initialization**: Extracts MISP integration configuration (API Root, Key, SSL settings) and action parameters.\n2. **Parameter Mapping**: Validates and converts string-based labels for Distribution, Threat Level, and Analysis into their corresponding MISP integer IDs.\n3. **Event Creation**: Sends a POST request to the MISP API to create the event with the provided metadata.\n4. **Optional Publication**: If the 'Publish' parameter is True, it makes a subsequent API call to publish the newly created event ID.\n5. **Result Processing**: Captures the new Event ID, adds the full event JSON to the action results, and provides a status message to the SOAR platform.","AiShortDescription":null,"ParametersDescription":null,"EntityTypes":[]}